# Git Conventions

- Conventional Commits: `<type>(<scope>): <description>`
- Types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, chore, ci, perf
- Scopes: backend, frontend, docs, ci, config, keywords, search, dedup, crawler, ocr, rag, writing
- Commit messages and code reviews in English
- Branch naming: `feat/<feature>`, `fix/<issue>`, `docs/<topic>`
- Remote: `git@github.com:sylvanding/omelette.git` (main branch)
- Always `git add` relevant files before commit, never commit .env
